race.comment: PANIGALE (2) resumes and has switched to the high-striking Clinton Taylor yard from a top Victorian stable. He's proven fresh and has raced well in much stronger than this. Owns a trial win here and Butler will give him every chance from the handy barrier. MAIKROW (1) just missed in a 65 at the Sunshine Coast before the break and then was caught wide at Eagle Farm first-up. This is a big step back in grade and Huxtable rides. Presents fitter and would be fighting out the finish at best. GILBERT'S GOLD (3) races forward and deserved the 55 win. Draws low and he has a strong second-up record. Should be right in the finish. DISCOVERED GOLD (5) missed a nose in a 55 heavily bet, and then the big money came again, and she delivered at a non-TAB at the track. She's going well enough to feature.
